<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05029c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05029c">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05029c"> 29(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> purge before communion</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Curiously enough, it was by no means uncommon to administer a <mark>purgative prior to partaking of this ritual meal</mark> to prevent the sacred food from being contaminated through contact with profane nourishment. That is the true explanation of the Catholic injunction to take the communion on an empty stomach. <small> J.T. Lloyd, <a name="GODE" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#GODE"><cite title="source">God-Eating</cite></a>, (1921) 35</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
